<%- include('header') %>

<section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
  <div class="text-center mb-12">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-black text-gold-400">Campaign Lore</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mt-3">The themes and theology woven into The Prismatic Soul.</p>
    <div class="gold-line w-32 mx-auto mt-4"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="space-y-10">

    <div class="glass rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-prism-400 mb-4">The Core Conflict</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
        The central conflict of The Prismatic Soul is between <strong class="text-gold-400">Grace and Giving</strong>
        (The Creator) and <strong class="text-crimson-500">Power and Taking</strong> (Vakos, the Eclipse of Gods).
        True godhood is defined by Charity, not raw strength.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="glass rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-prism-400 mb-4">The Splendor</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
        Also known as <em>The Brilliance</em> or <em>Intelligence</em>, the Splendor is the divine light and truth of the
        Creator woven into all reality. When a world is healthy, Splendor flows freely. When Vakos attacks, the world
        begins to wither as its Splendor is drained away.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-400 mt-3 leading-relaxed">
        Each world knows the Splendor by a different name &mdash; in Humblewood it is the Great Rhythm,
        in Oriven it flows unnamed through the veins of the earth.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="glass rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-prism-400 mb-4">The One True Creator</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
        The source of all Splendor. His true name is never spoken. Across the worlds he is known by many titles:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1 text-gray-400 text-sm list-inside">
        <li><strong class="text-gold-500">Oriven:</strong> The Sovereign</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gold-500">Humblewood:</strong> The Composer</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gold-500">Toril:</strong> The Luminous Being</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gold-500">Krynn:</strong> The High God</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gold-500">Spelljammer:</strong> The Prime Navigator</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gold-500">Feywild:</strong> The Father of Summer</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gold-500">The Crooked Moon:</strong> The White Lantern</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="glass rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-prism-400 mb-4">The Persistence of Self</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
        When heroes travel between worlds via <em>Grafting</em>, their physical form changes to match the setting
        &mdash; they may become Birdfolk in Humblewood or Elves in Faer&ucirc;n &mdash; but their <strong class="text-gold-400">Soul</strong>
        and heroic nature remain constant. The body is a vessel; the Splendor within is eternal.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="glass rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-prism-400 mb-4">The Narrative Arc</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-400 text-sm">
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-gold-400 font-display font-bold whitespace-nowrap">Phase 1:</span>
          <p><strong class="text-gray-300">The Interference (Oriven)</strong> &mdash; Heroes encounter Felicity, destroy the Chaos Bell, and open the path to the Woods Between Worlds.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-gold-400 font-display font-bold whitespace-nowrap">Phase 2:</span>
          <p><strong class="text-gray-300">The Crossing</strong> &mdash; The party enters the Woods, meets Silas, and undergoes Grafting into Birdfolk.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-gold-400 font-display font-bold whitespace-nowrap">Phase 3:</span>
          <p><strong class="text-gray-300">The Aspect of Fire (Humblewood)</strong> &mdash; Heroes address the fires ravaging Everden, uncovering Vexia's manipulation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-gold-400 font-display font-bold whitespace-nowrap">Phase 4:</span>
          <p><strong class="text-gray-300">The Multiverse</strong> &mdash; The party travels to Spelljammer, Faer&ucirc;n, the Feywild, and beyond, restoring Splendor world by world.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<%- include('footer') %>
